        <header>
            <div class="header-decoration"></div>
            <div class="chapter-label">Eugene Schwartz Framework</div>
            <h1>5 States of Awareness</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">Start at the precise point where your prospect is today</p>
        </header>

        <div class="insight-card">
            <h2>The Most Critical Insight</h2>
            <p>Your headline must start at the <span class="insight-highlight">precise point of awareness</span> the prospect has reached today. If your headline is too far ahead of or behind their awareness, it will fail.</p>
            <p style="margin-top: 16px;">Each stage is separated by a <span class="insight-highlight">psychological wall</span>. A headline that works for a "Most Aware" market will fail completely in an "Unaware" market.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bridge-section">
            <h2>üåâ The Headline's Real Job: The Bridge</h2>
            <div class="bridge-visual">
                <div class="bridge-point">Prospect's Current State</div>
                <div class="bridge-arrow">‚Üí</div>
                <div class="bridge-point">Your Headline</div>
                <div class="bridge-arrow">‚Üí</div>
                <div class="bridge-point">Your Product</div>
            </div>
            <p class="bridge-text">A headline does not necessarily need to sell the product or even mention its name. Its only job is to <strong>stop the prospect and compel them to read the second sentence</strong>. The headline acts as a bridge between the prospect's current state of mind and your product.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- DIAGNOSTIC TOOL -->
        <div class="diagnostic-section">
            <div class="diagnostic-header">
                <h2>üéØ Find Your Prospect's Awareness Stage</h2>
                <p>Answer these questions to identify where your audience is right now</p>
            </div>

            <div class="diagnostic-questions">
                <div class="diagnostic-question" data-question="1">
                    <div class="question-text">1. Does your prospect know your specific product exists?</div>
                    <div class="question-options">
                        <button class="option-btn" data-stage="1" onclick="selectOption(this, 1)">Yes, they know it and want it‚Äîthey just haven't bought yet</button>
                        <button class="option-btn" data-stage="2" onclick="selectOption(this, 1)">Yes, but they're not convinced it's better than competitors</button>
                        <button class="option-btn" data-stage="3" onclick="selectOption(this, 1)">No, but they know they want a solution</button>
                        <button class="option-btn" data-stage="4" onclick="selectOption(this, 1)">No, they have a problem but don't know solutions exist</button>
                        <button class="option-btn" data-stage="5" onclick="selectOption(this, 1)">No, they're unaware of the problem/desire itself</button>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="diagnostic-question" data-question="2">
                    <div class="question-text">2. What stops them from buying right now?</div>
                    <div class="question-options">
                        <button class="option-btn" data-stage="1" onclick="selectOption(this, 2)">Just need the right price or offer</button>
                        <button class="option-btn" data-stage="2" onclick="selectOption(this, 2)">Not sure it's better than alternatives</button>
                        <button class="option-btn" data-stage="3" onclick="selectOption(this, 2)">Don't know my specific product exists</button>
                        <button class="option-btn" data-stage="4" onclick="selectOption(this, 2)">Don't realize they have a solvable problem</button>
                        <button class="option-btn" data-stage="5" onclick="selectOption(this, 2)">Don't recognize they want/need anything</button>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="diagnostic-question" data-question="3">
                    <div class="question-text">3. What would make them respond to your headline?</div>
                    <div class="question-options">
                        <button class="option-btn" data-stage="1" onclick="selectOption(this, 3)">A great price or limited-time offer</button>
                        <button class="option-btn" data-stage="2" onclick="selectOption(this, 3)">New proof or a unique mechanism</button>
                        <button class="option-btn" data-stage="3" onclick="selectOption(this, 3)">A dramatic promise of their desired result</button>
                        <button class="option-btn" data-stage="4" onclick="selectOption(this, 3)">Recognition that their problem is real and solvable</button>
                        <button class="option-btn" data-stage="5" onclick="selectOption(this, 3)">Identifying with an emotion or situation</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

