                        <div class="info-section">
                            <div class="info-label">üéØ The Situation</div>
                            <p class="info-text">This is the most difficult and interesting stage. The prospect is either unaware of their desire/need or won't admit it to themselves. This requires the most sophisticated approach.</p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="strategy-box">
                            <div class="strategy-label">‚ú® Headline Strategy</div>
                            <p class="strategy-text">You <strong>cannot mention price, product, function, or desire</strong>. Instead, you must write an <strong>"Identification Headline"</strong> that calls your market together by echoing an emotion or attitude. You are <strong>selling the information in the ad</strong>, not the product itself.</p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="examples-box">
                            <div class="examples-label">üí° Examples</div>
                            <div class="example-item">"To the Young Woman Who Wants to Be Beautiful"</div>
                            <div class="example-item">"Why Men Crack"</div>
